title: For Sale/Trade:  Mateba Autorevolver
postcontent:
Mateba Sportiva Grifone autorevolver 8 Inch barrel. Excellent condition, beautiful bluing and grips. 

The Mateba Model 6 uses the recoil from firing to rotate the cylinder and cock the hammer, unlike conventional revolvers, which depend on the user physically pulling the trigger and/or cocking the hammer to actuate the weapon's mechanism of operation.
The Mateba Autorevolver's barrel alignment is different from most other revolvers. The barrel is aligned with the bottom of the cylinder instead of the top. This lowers the bore axis (line of the barrel) which directs the recoil in line with the shooter's hand thereby reducing the twisting motion or muzzle flip of normal revolvers. The gun's entire upper assembly (barrel, cylinder and frame) are mounted on rails on the lower frame, which houses the trigger, hammer, and grip, and recoils 1/2 of an inch, or 12.7mm, on firing. The rearward motion of the upper assembly cocks the hammer, and the cylinder is rotated on the forward stroke.

I'm busy during the day but you can text me at 573-864-7323 if you're interested. I will take any photos you want after I get home from work.

Comes with the disassembly tool and a few other small wrenches.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Be careful!
postcontent:
A lot going on lately with firearms/ ammo (Crazy $$$).  The "Ban" will not make it, doesn't have enough support.  Prices are starting to get back to the way they should be.

Just wait and get a firearm you can really enjoy, don't spend $2000 on a $500 gun.  

For M4/ AR types, if it does not cut it on the M4 Chart don't even bother, these are true specs that make a difference with a investment such as this.  Don't get mad at me, these are facts!
*M4 Chart-google docs, and updated on forums- chart not updated via Rob S anymore

And if it is an AK, read the forums, the lower end AK's are just lower end, you might get lucky, again you might just get a expensive aggravation.  Remember many of these AK's are kits/ parts put together in the US- too many variations.

If you need some advice/ help/ let me know, been doing this a while, plus not looking to get anything out of this- just helping fellow enthusiasts out- we are in this together!

*As a side note, seems ammo may be a while (slick guns current/ recent deals listed), mags and accessories are getting caught up.

title: For Sale:  Ham Radios- preppers, hunters, hobbiest
postcontent:
I saw a guy (same dude selling the overpriced corvette with no details, and a salesmans pitch)

The baofeng uv-5ra (newest model) is a Chinese made ham radio that does what the heavy hitting jap radios do, but for the price of your average Walmart junk walkie talkie. 

 I'm new to ham (studying for license, which isn't hard) but I can confirm these are amazing, way better than a cb also. I heard people from Beaverton (I am in Portland) also people from Hawaii, Cali, Georgia, and somewhere else I forget, camping a frequency as if it was a chat room just talking which I tumbled upon using the scanner button right out of the box.

For $44-$50 bucks having that type of power? Incredible. Just be aware, arms list is full of people trying to make a dishonest buck right now.. Ignorance is no excuse when you find yourself ripped off bad, do your homework.

If your into that electro magnetic pulse stuff, look into faraday cages, can make them yourself, or just buy some lead, and bury the radio. If anything happens you will have god like powers (communication haha)

But really.. Can't go wrong with these radios, and from what I've heard listening ( not keying in) is that the people n the waves want more good folks out there talking.

For under a hundred bucks you could buy Gordon wests audiobook course training you for the test to take get your license.

A baofeng dual band radio.

Extra rechargeable lithium battery packs for the radio

And pay for the test itself.

I know this isn't exactly what armslist was designed for ( they really need to add a forum) but I am sick of seeing people raise prices for personal gain so I felt the need to rant a little at least rant on the dude selling something for twice as more as it is brand new and n stock.

title: For Sale:  BARRETT REC7 5.56 NATO
postcontent: Compact, accurate and completely trustworthy, the REC7 is designed specifically for situations in which there’s no room for error. Styled in the familiar AR configuration, it’s a no-nonsense rifle you can trust with anything—including your life. This tough-as-nails rifle was designed specifically to answer the call for a low-maintenance, enhanced reliability carbine. The REC7 rifle’s dependability stems largely from its innovative operating system. Using a minimum number of parts, the piston system separates heat and powder residue from the bolt carrier and trigger assembly. The rifle runs cool and clean, reducing maintenance requirements and increasing endurance. The patented chrome-lined fluted gas block prevents excessive carbon buildup from operation under adverse conditions. The one-piece 17-4 stainless piston transfers energy to the anti-tilt bolt carrier. Machined from a monolithic block of 8620 steel, the carrier features an integral piston strike face. The Barrett Enhanced Bolt is made from high-strength 9310 steel. The bolt is designed specifically for use in the piston operated REC7, not just adapted from a direct gas bolt. The bolt’s gas-ring-free design is easy to clean. Reinforced at critical areas, every bolt is proofed and magnetic-particle inspected to guarantee reliable performance. At the heart of the operating system is a nitrided, two-position, forward-venting gas plug that retains the piston. The piston can be accessed through the front of the gas block without removing the handguard so optical sights or laser devices do not need to be zeroed after routine maintenance. The REC7 rifle’s forged 7075 aluminum upper and lower receivers are Type 3 hardcoat anodized. The lower houses an ultra-dependable single-stage trigger. The upper supports a free-floated, hammer-forged, chrome-lined barrel with M4 feed ramps machined into the receiver and the barrel extension. A mil-spec A2 flash hider protects the muzzle.
